fields.name: Other Insights
fields.definition: Insights that do not fall in any other existing category

fields.name: Aha Moment
fields.definition: A point in time when a customer or user suddenly realizes the value or benefit of a product or service, leading to increased engagement and satisfaction.

fields.name: Churn Signal
fields.definition: An indication that a customer or user is likely to stop using a product or service, often based on a decrease in engagement or satisfaction.

fields.name: Price Mention
fields.definition: A reference made by a customer or user to the cost or pricing of a product or service, which may indicate price sensitivity or a willingness to pay.

fields.name: Competitor Mention
fields.definition: A reference made by a customer or user to a competing product or service, which may indicate a comparison of features, pricing, or overall satisfaction.

fields.name: Pain Point
fields.definition: A specific problem or frustration experienced by a customer or user when using a product or service.

fields.name: Feature Request
fields.definition: A suggestion or demand from a customer or user for a new feature or functionality to be added to a product or service.
